EXPRESS.JS

(1) A web framework and a tool that simplifies building web apps and APIS using JS on the server side.
(2) Express is an open-source that is developed and maintained by the Node.js foundation.

CREATING A SERVER USING EXPRESS

Steps:

(i) create a folder
(ii) npm init -y
(iii) npm i express
(iv) create a file <fileName>.js in the folder
(v) npm i nodemon // this updates the server in the runtime
(vi) In package.json:

    "scripts": {
    "start": "node index.js",
    "dev": "nodemon index.js"
  }

(vii) npm run dev